1-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/self-esteem-2000x1270-1-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/self-esteem">自尊</a>歌手丽贝卡·露西·泰勒将获得谢菲尔德大学的荣誉学位。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/big-reads/self-esteem-cover-interview-2021-rebecca-taylor-prioritise-pleasure-3024342">自尊：“我想在我的议程中利用流行音乐的可口性来对付特洛伊木马”</a><br /></strong></li></ul><p>这位出生于罗瑟勒姆的音乐家将被授予南约克郡大学荣誉音乐博士学位，仪式将于今天晚些时候（7 月 17 日）举行。</p><p>该大学在其官方推特页面上宣布了这一消息，该页面赞扬了泰勒作为艺术家的能力以及她对鼓励包容性和多样性的奉献。</p><p> “我们很高兴地宣布，丽贝卡·露西·泰勒（又名自尊）今天因其在音乐方面的成功以及对包容性和多样性的公开倡导而被授予荣誉学位，”更新中写道。</p><p>今天晚些时候，她将与其他 11 名知名人士以及今年的毕业生一起被授予荣誉学位。</p><p>在谈到该奖项时，泰勒表示：“能够获得谢菲尔德大学的荣誉博士学位，我感到非常高兴。我全心全意地爱谢菲尔德，得到这样的认可增强了我为像我这样的音乐人做出巨大改变的梦想。我感到无比激动、振奋、充满活力！”</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet" data-width="550" data-dnt="true"><p lang="en" dir="ltr">我们很高兴地宣布，丽贝卡·露西·泰勒（又名“自尊”）今天因其在音乐方面的成功以及对包容性和多样性的公开倡导而被授予荣誉学位！关注这个空间了解更多…… <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/14.0.0/72x72/1f440.png" alt="👀" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> <a href="https://t.co/8smQVXCFo0">https://t.co/8smQVXCFo0</a> <a href="https://twitter.com/SELFESTEEM___?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">@SELFESTEEM___</a> <a href="https://t.co/HxGALxsHYg">pic.twitter.com/HxGALxsHYg</a></p><p> — 谢菲尔德大学 (@sheffielduni) <a href="https://twitter.com/sheffielduni/status/1680820257995341826?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">2023 年 7 月 17 日</a></p></blockquote><p><script async src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js" charset="utf-8"></script></p><p>这位 36 岁的音乐家已经成为谢菲尔德的骄傲大使，并<a href="https://www.nme.com/blogs/festivals-blog/self-esteem-glastonbury-2022-review-setlist-photos-meadowhall-3256085">在去年的格拉斯顿伯里音乐节上表演，其服装灵感来自该市的购物中心 Meadowhall</a> 。</p><p>她于 2021 年发行的第二张专辑《Prioritise Pleasure》获得了水星音乐奖提名。 It also received <a href="https://www.nme.com/en_au/reviews/self-esteem-prioritise-pleasure-review-3074841">a four-star review from <em>NME</em></a> , who described the LP as both “sharply witty” but showcasing “moments of sincerity [which] shine brightly”.</p><p> That same year, Taylor also <a href="https://www.nme.com/big-reads/self-esteem-cover-interview-2021-rebecca-taylor-prioritise-pleasure-3024342">appeared as an <em>NME</em> cover star</a> , and discussed how her sexuality plays a role in her music. “Realising my sexuality wasn&#39;t a massive deal, but it did make me feel odd about what I presented to an audience,” she said at the time. “Having to sing songs that couldn&#39;t represent just my feelings was just very restrictive.”</p><p> “It would be uncomfortable for me to sing a generic song about nothing,” she added. “There&#39;s people who make music which is just like, &#39;La, la, la&#39;, and they fit some words in it… Having nothing to say? Can&#39;t imagine it.” </p><figure id="attachment_3405743" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3405743" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3405743" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-2023-self-esteem-getty.jpg" alt="自尊" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-2023-self-esteem-getty.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-2023-self-esteem-getty-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-2023-self-esteem-getty-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-2023-self-esteem-getty-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-2023-self-esteem-getty-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/live-2023-self-esteem-getty-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3405743" class="wp-caption-text"> Self Esteem performing at the 3Olympia Theatre Dublin on February 26, 2023. Credit: Debbie Hickey/Getty Images.</figcaption></figure><p> In other news, earlier this year, it was announced that Self Esteem is <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/self-esteem-announces-huge-hometown-headline-show-in-sheffield-3430595">set to play a massive homecoming show in Sheffield</a> . Announced as one of the headliners for the Rock N Roll Circus event at the Don Valley Bowl (September 2), she will be joined by <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/confidence-man">Confidence Man</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/bimini">Bimini</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/arctic-monkeys">Arctic Monkeys</a> tribute band Arctic Numpties, the latter of whom she recently <a href="https://www.nme.com/en_au/news/music/self-esteem-arctic-monkeys-tribute-band-perform-there-d-better-be-a-mirrorball-3418843">joined on stage at a gig in her hometown</a> .</p><p> The new show is being billed as the final show of her <a href="https://www.nme.com/en_au/reviews/self-esteem-prioritise-pleasure-review-3074841">&#39;Prioritise Pleasure&#39;</a> era, supporting her second album.</p><p> At the start of the month, Self Esteem also performed at Wembley Stadium as an opener for <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/blur">Blur</a> . Taking place on Saturday (July 8), <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/jockstrap">Jockstrap</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sleaford-mods">Sleaford Mods</a> also acted as support for the band, who performed one of <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/live/blur-live-in-london-wembley-setlist-photos-review-3466214">two mammoth reunion shows</a> at the London venue.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/self-esteem-awarded-honorary-degree-from-university-of-sheffield-3469314">Self Esteem to be awarded honorary degree from University of Sheffield</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
